cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper discusses the use of social media, specifically microblogging (Twitter), by nonprofit organizations for communication and engagement with stakeholders. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) which deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. The paper also involves analysis of data and communication practices, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of Twitter for information dissemination and engagement could also relate to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
